WEBVTT

00:01.686 --> 00:04.788
♪ Men. ♪

00:04.852 --> 00:09.022
No... No, Charlie.

00:09.023 --> 00:10.457
It's mine.

00:10.458 --> 00:12.025
What?

00:12.026 --> 00:13.627
Give it back.

00:13.628 --> 00:14.962
Ow!

00:14.963 --> 00:17.998
Mom! Charlie hit me!

00:17.999 --> 00:20.767
Oh, okay.

00:20.768 --> 00:22.903
Consuela, Charlie hit me.

00:22.904 --> 00:25.005
Ow!

00:25.006 --> 00:28.041
Mom, Consuela hit me.

00:28.042 --> 00:31.244
God. Here we go again.

00:31.245 --> 00:34.781
I'll run away,
then you'll be sorry.

00:34.782 --> 00:37.751
Ow! Mom, Charlie's making me
hit myself.

00:40.722 --> 00:42.556
Hey. What are
you doing up?

00:42.557 --> 00:44.891
Your brother's talking
in his sleep again.

00:44.892 --> 00:46.360
No kidding.
what about?

00:46.361 --> 00:49.062
Some childhood dream about
you making him hit himself.

00:49.063 --> 00:51.999
What childhood?
That was last week.

00:53.134 --> 00:54.634
<i>Sports Center?</i>

00:54.635 --> 00:57.537
Yeah. I'm making my picks
for tomorrow's games.

00:57.538 --> 00:59.106
Really, Charlie?

00:59.107 --> 01:00.807
Taking the points
against Georgetown?

01:00.808 --> 01:02.142
No.

01:02.143 --> 01:03.877
If you want to throw
your money away,

01:03.878 --> 01:06.179
why don't you just get married
without a prenup.

01:07.215 --> 01:09.416
You know something I don't?

01:09.417 --> 01:11.852
So far this year, Georgetown's
covered the spread

01:11.853 --> 01:13.086
eight times out of ten.

01:13.087 --> 01:15.822
Wow, you bet
college basketball?

01:15.823 --> 01:17.791
Only idiots bet
college basketball.

01:19.093 --> 01:20.060
No offense.

01:20.061 --> 01:22.029
Then how do you know
all this stuff?

01:22.030 --> 01:23.597
I worked for a
sports book in Vegas.

01:23.598 --> 01:25.065
Then I opened my own
little business

01:25.066 --> 01:27.134
in the back of a candle shop
in Sherman Oaks.

01:27.135 --> 01:30.237
I always wondered how those
places stayed in business.

01:30.238 --> 01:33.306
Yeah, so did the IRS.

01:33.307 --> 01:35.776
So they nailed you
for running a book?

01:35.777 --> 01:37.811
No. They nailed me
for running a candle store

01:37.812 --> 01:39.946
that made a quarter of a million
dollars a year

01:39.947 --> 01:41.882
without selling
one freakin' candle.

01:43.518 --> 01:45.919
Okay, so no on Georgetown.

01:45.920 --> 01:48.555
Does Alan know
about this?

01:48.556 --> 01:49.956
He knows about the candle store.

01:49.957 --> 01:51.691
Let's just keep
the other part between us.

01:51.692 --> 01:55.562
Yeah, he's kind of prissy
about moral stuff like gambling.

01:55.563 --> 01:56.563
Yeah, he is.

01:56.564 --> 01:57.731
And drinking.

01:57.732 --> 01:59.466
Well, that's only because
when he drinks,

01:59.467 --> 02:01.701
he gets all weepy
and then he pukes.

02:01.702 --> 02:02.936
And whoring.

02:02.937 --> 02:05.138
No, he doesn't have
a moral problem with that.

02:05.139 --> 02:07.541
He's just cheap
and he likes to cuddle.

02:07.542 --> 02:11.545
Well, don't worry-- your sordid
gambling past will be our secret.

02:11.546 --> 02:14.214
I'm glad to know I can trust you.
Well, of course you can.

02:14.215 --> 02:16.817
Hey, I never told him about your
little soft-core film career.

02:16.818 --> 02:18.718
Oh, God.

02:18.719 --> 02:21.088
You saw <i>Cinnamon's Buns?</i>

02:21.089 --> 02:24.524
Not all the way through.

02:26.561 --> 02:28.462
Although I am
very familiar with

02:28.463 --> 02:30.964
the bakery shop scene
in the middle.

02:31.899 --> 02:34.067
You know, with
the frosting gun?

02:34.068 --> 02:36.470
I was 19, I needed the money.

02:36.471 --> 02:38.805
They promised me
it would be tasteful.

02:38.806 --> 02:40.707
It looked very tasteful.

02:40.708 --> 02:43.009
And delicious.

02:43.010 --> 02:45.579
Yum, yum.

02:45.580 --> 02:47.581
Glad to hear you enjoyed it.

02:47.582 --> 02:49.583
Oh, yeah. Although I don't
think you were well-served

02:49.584 --> 02:50.684
by the screenplay.

02:50.685 --> 02:52.018
What screenplay?

02:52.019 --> 02:54.254
There was just a greasy
little guy behind the camera

02:54.255 --> 02:56.223
saying, "Do this, do that.
More frosting."

02:57.024 --> 03:00.127
It's kind of weird.
In some way,

03:00.128 --> 03:03.196
you and I have more in common
than you and my brother.

03:03.197 --> 03:06.867
All right, let's take something
off the table right away.

03:06.868 --> 03:08.602
What's that?
My ass.

03:08.603 --> 03:10.770
That's not what
I was getting at...

03:10.771 --> 03:12.873
Seriously, Charlie,
in spite of my past,

03:12.874 --> 03:15.275
I'm just a nice
little Valley soccer mom now.

03:15.276 --> 03:17.544
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
soccer mom?

03:17.545 --> 03:19.913
Your kid's a
babbling pothead.

03:19.914 --> 03:21.414
He played soccer
when he was ten.

03:21.415 --> 03:22.682
He scored two goals.

03:22.683 --> 03:23.717
In one game?

03:23.718 --> 03:24.818
In one season. Shut up.

03:24.819 --> 03:26.920
The point is,

03:26.921 --> 03:28.488
I am way past guys like you.

03:28.489 --> 03:30.590
What do you mean
guys like me?

03:30.591 --> 03:32.826
I mean guys that I have
to dip in ammonia

03:32.827 --> 03:34.427
before I'd let them
anywhere near me.

03:34.428 --> 03:36.796
Oh. Those guys.

03:38.232 --> 03:40.066
Well, as long as
we're being honest,

03:40.067 --> 03:42.369
I'm perfectly happy with the
way things are between us.

03:42.370 --> 03:44.437
Besides, you're
really good for Alan.

03:44.438 --> 03:45.972
Thank you.
Yeah, yeah, no,

03:45.973 --> 03:48.475
y-you're, you're smart,
you're strong,

03:48.476 --> 03:52.646
you're self-sufficient,
and he's, well... not.

03:52.647 --> 03:54.548
I think
you underestimate your brother.

03:54.549 --> 03:57.150
It's not an estimate.
I already got the bill.

03:57.151 --> 04:00.086
You'll see, one of these days
he's gonna surprise you.

04:00.087 --> 04:02.689
And one of these days I'm
gonna die of liver failure.

04:02.690 --> 04:04.758
Want to lay odds
which happens first?

04:05.993 --> 04:09.062
Good night, Charlie.
Good night.

