04:53.543 --> 04:55.844
Don't worry,
she's leaving very soon.

04:55.845 --> 04:57.112
I'm not worried.

04:57.113 --> 04:58.714
Actually, I like
having her around.

04:58.715 --> 05:00.315
You not so much.

05:00.316 --> 05:01.683
Thank you.

05:01.684 --> 05:03.618
That never ceases to be funny.

05:03.619 --> 05:06.455
Ah, cinnamon buns!

05:12.495 --> 05:14.096
How did you know?

05:14.097 --> 05:15.263
I bought them.

05:15.264 --> 05:17.232
Oh, right, cinnamon buns.

05:17.233 --> 05:19.000
Who doesn't love cinnamon buns?

05:19.001 --> 05:20.469
Charlie!

05:20.470 --> 05:21.603
What, what, what?

05:21.604 --> 05:22.771
Alan bought cinnamon buns.

05:22.772 --> 05:24.106
With frosting.

05:25.541 --> 05:28.009
Oh.

05:28.811 --> 05:30.312
Yum.

05:33.149 --> 05:34.516
All right, honey.

05:34.517 --> 05:35.550
I'll see you later.

05:35.551 --> 05:36.952
Oh. I'll call you
after work.

05:36.953 --> 05:38.153
See ya, Charlie.

05:38.154 --> 05:40.122
Hey, Lynds, has your son
picked a college yet?

05:40.123 --> 05:41.790
Uh, no. Why?

05:42.492 --> 05:44.126
Well, I was
just wondering

05:44.127 --> 05:46.695
if he were to choose
between say...

05:48.030 --> 05:50.465
North Carolina and Kentucky...

05:51.934 --> 05:54.136
...which one would you encourage
him to pick?

05:54.137 --> 05:55.837
Keeping in mind that as
an out-of-state resident,

05:55.838 --> 05:57.906
Kentucky is two-and-a-half times
more expensive.

05:59.342 --> 06:03.011
I'd still go with Kentucky.
It's a better school.

06:03.012 --> 06:04.513
Interesting.

06:04.514 --> 06:06.882
Well, I hope he gets in.

06:06.883 --> 06:08.583
Thanks. Bye.

06:08.584 --> 06:10.419
Bye.

06:10.420 --> 06:12.788
What was that all about?
Hmm?

06:12.789 --> 06:15.424
Since when do you care
about her kid's education?

06:15.425 --> 06:16.758
Young people are our future,
Alan.

06:16.759 --> 06:17.993
I care about them all.

06:17.994 --> 06:20.929
Oh, please. The only young
people you care about

06:20.930 --> 06:24.132
are sliding down a pole to grab
dollar bills out of your mouth.

06:24.133 --> 06:28.069
Those aren't dollar bills--
those are 20s.

06:29.338 --> 06:30.739
And when did you become
such a cynic?

06:30.740 --> 06:32.207
And when did you become
so interested

06:32.208 --> 06:33.942
in the comings and goings
of my girlfriend--

06:33.943 --> 06:35.410
or what her kid's up to?

06:35.411 --> 06:36.778
Whoa, whoa, chill.

06:36.779 --> 06:38.079
No, no, I will not chill.

06:38.080 --> 06:40.315
And what was all that about
liking having her around?

06:40.316 --> 06:42.083
Nothing.
I like having her around.

06:42.084 --> 06:44.286
Yeah, but around what?

06:44.287 --> 06:45.487
Excuse me?

06:45.488 --> 06:48.623
I think when you say "around,"
you mean under.

06:48.624 --> 06:50.859
Don't go down that road, Alan.

06:50.860 --> 06:52.794
Oh, oh, why shouldn't
I go down that road?

06:52.795 --> 06:55.197
Is it slippery when wet?

06:55.198 --> 06:57.799
Are you out of your mind?
What's gotten into you?

06:57.800 --> 07:00.602
Oh, I think a better question
would be what's gotten into you?

07:00.603 --> 07:03.271
I mean, who have you
gotten into?

07:03.272 --> 07:05.807
Alan, Alan, listen to me
very carefully.

07:05.808 --> 07:08.009
I have not had sex
with your girlfriend.

07:08.010 --> 07:09.344
Oh, so it's still
in the planning stages.

07:09.345 --> 07:10.745
No.
But you do want her?

07:10.746 --> 07:12.614
No.
Why not? What's wrong with her?

07:12.615 --> 07:15.116
Nothing. She's terrific.

07:15.117 --> 07:16.718
So you do want her!

07:16.719 --> 07:18.854
Alan, believe me,
when it comes to Lyndsey,

07:18.855 --> 07:21.089
you have absolutely nothing
to worry about.

07:21.090 --> 07:23.692
Uh-huh, uh-huh. That's what
you said about Wendy Freidman

07:23.693 --> 07:25.694
and Kathy Bell
and Amy Driskell.

07:25.695 --> 07:26.862
Who?

07:26.863 --> 07:28.964
They're all girls that
you stole from me.

07:28.965 --> 07:30.031
What are you talking about?

07:30.032 --> 07:31.032
I never stole anybody from you.

07:31.033 --> 07:32.801
Wendy Freidman.

07:32.802 --> 07:34.503
Sixth grade,
Halloween party.

07:34.504 --> 07:35.737
I went to get her punch.
When I came back,

07:35.738 --> 07:37.506
you were bobbing
for her apples.

07:37.507 --> 07:39.741
Innocent fun.

07:39.742 --> 07:41.877
Oh... Kathy Bell,
ninth grade.

07:41.878 --> 07:43.178
I brought her home to work
on our science project.

07:43.179 --> 07:44.379
I went to the bathroom.

07:44.380 --> 07:46.515
When I came back, you
were teaching her French.

07:46.516 --> 07:48.750
Harmless horseplay.

07:48.751 --> 07:50.986
Amy Driskell,
sophomore year.

07:50.987 --> 07:52.687
First girl who let me
get to second base.

07:52.688 --> 07:54.556
All right, her I nailed.

07:54.557 --> 07:57.359
Wait, wait, wait.
You nailed her?

07:57.360 --> 07:59.928
Everybody nailed her.
That was her thing.

07:59.929 --> 08:01.997
It took me six months

08:01.998 --> 08:03.265
just to touch her right boob!

08:03.266 --> 08:06.167
Wow, you really missed
the signals, didn't you?

08:06.168 --> 08:07.168
What signals?

08:07.169 --> 08:08.270
Well, in my case,

08:08.271 --> 08:09.571
it was her
taking off her sweater

08:09.572 --> 08:11.206
and saying, "Quick, do me
before Alan gets back

08:11.207 --> 08:12.474
from his trumpet lesson."

08:17.079 --> 08:19.614
Clarinet. I didn't have
the lip for trumpet.

08:19.615 --> 08:21.850
Apparently, you didn't have the
lip for Amy Driskell, either.

08:23.886 --> 08:26.421
But all that
was a long time ago.

08:26.422 --> 08:28.490
You're with Lyndsey now,
and what's important

08:28.491 --> 08:30.926
is that I wish you both
a long and happy life together.

08:30.927 --> 08:33.061
Really?
From the bottom of my heart.

08:33.062 --> 08:35.764
Okay.

08:35.765 --> 08:37.097
Thank you.

08:37.099 --> 08:39.534
You're welcome.

08:41.136 --> 08:42.837
Though I'd still like you
to move out.

08:42.837 --> 08:45.507
Got it.

08:47.510 --> 08:48.910
Soon.

08:48.911 --> 08:50.178
Right.

08:53.549 --> 08:55.884
No, I guess that's about it.

08:57.987 --> 08:59.354
Amy Driskell.

08:59.355 --> 09:02.791
"No, Alan, I'm saving myself
for Jesus."

09:04.226 --> 09:05.827
♪ Men. ♪

09:07.063 --> 09:09.164
Come on in.

09:09.165 --> 09:10.432
Hey.

09:10.433 --> 09:12.667
Wow, the place looks great.

09:12.668 --> 09:14.536
Doesn't it?

09:15.371 --> 09:17.272
Even better than
before I accidentally

09:17.273 --> 09:19.274
almost burned it
to the ground.

09:19.275 --> 09:21.409
Yeah.

09:21.410 --> 09:22.944
You're welcome.

09:22.945 --> 09:24.512
Come here.

09:24.513 --> 09:26.214
I want to give
you something.

09:26.215 --> 09:27.649
Oh. Fooling around?

09:27.650 --> 09:29.184
On the new couch?

09:29.185 --> 09:30.685
Get your mind
out of the gutter.

09:30.686 --> 09:31.886
I haven't Scotchgarded yet.

09:31.887 --> 09:33.688
Oh.

09:33.689 --> 09:34.889
Here.

09:34.890 --> 09:36.324
A house key?

09:36.325 --> 09:38.593
Uh-huh.
For this house?

09:38.594 --> 09:41.329
Maybe we're not ready
to move in together,

09:41.330 --> 09:43.264
but I want you to feel
like you can come and go

09:43.265 --> 09:44.332
without checking in with me.

09:44.333 --> 09:46.534
Wow. Wow. Thank you.

09:46.535 --> 09:50.005
In a lot of ways, this isn't
just the key to your house,

09:50.006 --> 09:52.240
it's the key to your heart.

09:52.241 --> 09:54.976
Don't gay it up.

09:56.879 --> 09:58.947
Now listen,
I'm thinking of having

09:58.948 --> 10:00.315
a housewarming party
next Saturday.

10:00.316 --> 10:01.483
Great. What can I do?

10:01.484 --> 10:02.717
You can help me
with the guest list.

10:02.718 --> 10:03.885
Okay.

10:03.886 --> 10:05.487
What would you say
about inviting

10:05.488 --> 10:07.455
Judith and Herb?
My ex-wife?

10:07.456 --> 10:08.823
They live right
across the street,

10:08.824 --> 10:10.358
and Herb is always
so sweet to me.

10:10.359 --> 10:12.060
That's because every time
Herb looks at you,

10:12.061 --> 10:14.229
he's pretending
you're wet and naked.

10:14.230 --> 10:16.231
All right. Fine.
I won't invite him.

10:16.232 --> 10:18.066
It would probably just
upset Judith anyway.

10:18.067 --> 10:19.267
Yeah, you're right.

10:19.268 --> 10:21.503
You know what?
Let's invite them.

10:22.238 --> 10:23.672
Take the high road.

10:23.673 --> 10:25.707
All right.
What about Berta?

10:25.708 --> 10:27.342
Oh, no. I don't think so.

10:27.343 --> 10:29.244
Why not?
She's kind of mean to me.

10:29.245 --> 10:30.545
Oh, honey.

10:30.546 --> 10:32.447
That's just 'cause
she doesn't like you.

10:32.448 --> 10:34.783
Fine. Berta.

10:34.784 --> 10:36.384
And Jake.

10:36.385 --> 10:38.420
Oh, of course. Great.
And Charlie.

10:38.421 --> 10:40.355
There it is.

10:40.356 --> 10:41.322
There what is?

10:41.323 --> 10:42.924
Charlie. Why do
you want Charlie

10:42.925 --> 10:44.125
to come to your party?

10:44.126 --> 10:45.360
Why wouldn't I?
When this place burned down,

10:45.361 --> 10:46.528
he took us in.

10:46.529 --> 10:47.862
He took me in seven years ago,

10:47.863 --> 10:50.031
and I don't feel a need
to invite him.

10:50.032 --> 10:51.599
Oh, come on.

10:51.600 --> 10:53.568
He's a great guy.
I really like him.

10:53.569 --> 10:55.503
Of course you do.
All the women like Charlie.

10:55.504 --> 10:56.638
"All the women"?

10:56.639 --> 10:57.605
Wendy Freidman,

10:57.606 --> 10:58.606
Kathy Bell,

10:58.607 --> 10:59.607
Amy Driskell.

10:59.608 --> 11:00.642
Who?

11:00.643 --> 11:02.944
And now Lyndsey MacElroy.

11:02.945 --> 11:03.978
Oh, please.

11:03.979 --> 11:05.346
Charlie and I are just friends.

11:05.347 --> 11:07.549
Oh, no, no, no, my brother
does not befriend women,

11:07.550 --> 11:08.550
he befouls them.

11:08.551 --> 11:11.853
Are you saying
you don't trust me?

11:11.854 --> 11:13.722
Oh, no, no, no,
I don't trust Charlie.

11:13.723 --> 11:15.290
For him,
you're unexplored territory.

11:15.291 --> 11:18.193
At some point, he's gonna try
and plant his flag in you.

11:19.195 --> 11:21.529
And when I say "flag,"
I mean his...

11:23.365 --> 11:24.733
...flag.

11:24.734 --> 11:28.236
Okay, you're out of your mind.

11:28.237 --> 11:29.370
Yeah, well, be that as it may,

11:29.371 --> 11:31.039
I do not want you hanging out
with my brother.

11:31.040 --> 11:33.208
I mean, you know, you
can be courteous to him.

11:33.209 --> 11:34.209
You know, like, "Hey, Charlie,

11:34.210 --> 11:35.710
you got some vomit
on your shoe,"

11:35.711 --> 11:38.379
or, you know, "Hey, Charlie,
do you need me to move my car

11:38.380 --> 11:40.615
so your hooker can park
her pink Camaro?"

11:40.616 --> 11:43.084
Do you realize
how insulting this is?

11:43.085 --> 11:46.121
You don't get to tell me who I
can and can't be friends with.

11:46.122 --> 11:48.223
Hey, it's just Charlie.
I gave you Herb and Berta.

11:48.224 --> 11:50.925
You know what, I made a mistake.

11:50.926 --> 11:53.094
Well, I forgive you.

11:53.095 --> 11:55.230
Give me my key back.

11:55.231 --> 11:56.965
What?
Give it to me.

11:56.966 --> 11:58.199
Then how can I
come and go?

11:58.200 --> 12:00.502
You can forget coming,
you're just gonna be going.

12:00.503 --> 12:01.770
But I-I don't
understand.

12:01.771 --> 12:03.004
We were doing so good.

12:03.005 --> 12:05.740
We were, then you started
talking and spoiled it.

12:05.741 --> 12:08.243
Okay, okay,
ju-just to clarify--

12:08.244 --> 12:09.611
you're not as angry with me now

12:09.612 --> 12:11.880
as you were when I
burned down your house?

12:13.649 --> 12:17.118
Okay, we'll talk after
you've gained some perspective.

12:18.521 --> 12:20.755
♪ Men. ♪

12:23.528 --> 12:25.529
♪ Men. ♪

12:25.530 --> 12:26.997
Jake, Berta, let's go!

12:26.998 --> 12:28.698
Party train's leaving.

12:30.034 --> 12:31.735
That what you're wearing
to Lyndsey's housewarming?

12:31.736 --> 12:33.003
I'm not going.

12:33.004 --> 12:34.004
Why not?

12:34.005 --> 12:35.439
She and I had a little argument.

12:35.440 --> 12:36.573
Aw, that's too bad.

12:36.574 --> 12:38.842
Jake, Berta, let's go!

12:38.843 --> 12:40.877
Charlie.

12:41.412 --> 12:42.879
If you do what I think

12:42.880 --> 12:45.782
you're gonna do, I swear to God
I will never speak to you again.

12:45.783 --> 12:47.250
Oh, really?

12:47.251 --> 12:48.885
Then by all means,
tell me exactly

12:48.886 --> 12:50.420
what you think I'm gonna do.

12:50.421 --> 12:52.255
You know what I'm talking about.

12:52.256 --> 12:54.057
All right, all right,

12:54.058 --> 12:56.493
I'm gonna run this down for you
one last time.

12:56.494 --> 12:58.595
I have no interest in Lyndsey
other than as a friend,

12:58.596 --> 13:00.130
and she has even less
interest in me.

13:00.131 --> 13:01.498
I don't believe you.

13:01.499 --> 13:02.732
Okay, fine, you're right.

13:02.733 --> 13:03.934
I'm going over
to your girlfriend's house,

13:03.935 --> 13:05.268
and I'm gonna do her
right on the couch!

13:05.269 --> 13:07.504
No, you won't.
Why not?

13:07.505 --> 13:09.573
Couch isn't Scotchgarded yet.

13:11.609 --> 13:13.910
Hey, Charlie, did you remember
to get the housewarming gift?

13:13.911 --> 13:15.579
Jake's got it. Jake!

13:21.285 --> 13:22.219
Very funny.

13:22.220 --> 13:23.920
We thought so.

13:24.989 --> 13:26.189
How come you
aren't dressed?

13:26.190 --> 13:27.491
He and Lyndsey had a fight.

13:27.492 --> 13:28.959
Oh. That sucks.

13:28.960 --> 13:30.460
See ya.

13:31.362 --> 13:32.362
So you're just gonna

13:32.363 --> 13:33.430
sit here all night?

13:33.431 --> 13:34.698
Oh, I'll be fine.

13:34.699 --> 13:36.166
Oh, I'm sure you will.

13:36.167 --> 13:39.269
But if you get bored, there's
a load of laundry in the dryer

13:39.270 --> 13:40.837
you could fluff and fold.

13:40.838 --> 13:43.073
So you want me to do your job?

13:43.074 --> 13:45.475
Somebody has to.

13:46.444 --> 13:48.879
Well, I guess there's nothing

13:48.880 --> 13:52.782
left to say except
you're an idiot.

13:54.585 --> 13:57.420
I may be an idiot,
but at least I'm home by myself

13:57.421 --> 14:00.924
reading <i>Moby Dick.</i>

14:00.925 --> 14:03.126
Upside down.

14:08.466 --> 14:10.667
Might as well.

14:12.970 --> 14:15.939
Maybe she'll like me better.

14:15.940 --> 14:18.208
♪ Men. ♪

14:18.209 --> 14:19.209
Where's your
friend Eldridge?

14:19.210 --> 14:20.377
He lives
here, right?

14:20.378 --> 14:22.045
Yeah, he's hiding in his room.

14:22.046 --> 14:23.146
How come?

14:23.147 --> 14:25.348
He gets really paranoid
when he's high...

14:25.349 --> 14:27.083
...ding in his room.

14:27.084 --> 14:29.319
I just came to get him
these snacks. Bye.

14:29.320 --> 14:31.855
Amateurs.

14:33.858 --> 14:34.991
Nice party.

14:34.992 --> 14:35.926
Thanks.

14:35.927 --> 14:37.761
So give me the
lay of the land.

14:37.762 --> 14:39.930
You mean who in this land
can you lay?

14:39.931 --> 14:41.765
If you will.

14:41.766 --> 14:43.533
All right.

14:43.534 --> 14:45.068
Hot redhead by the bar--

14:45.069 --> 14:46.036
that's Wanda.

14:46.037 --> 14:47.604
Recently came out of
a terrible marriage.

14:47.605 --> 14:49.239
Nice, nice.

14:49.240 --> 14:50.440
What else you got?

14:50.441 --> 14:53.310
Pretty blonde on the couch--
that's Terry.

14:53.311 --> 14:55.478
She divorced her husband
to be a lesbian.

14:55.479 --> 14:57.380
How's that working
out for Terry?

14:57.381 --> 14:59.349
See the dirty look
she's giving Wanda?

15:00.551 --> 15:01.785
Oh.

15:01.786 --> 15:03.853
I think I see
an opening.

15:03.854 --> 15:05.522
And by that you mean...?

15:05.523 --> 15:07.390
I wasn't being subtle;
I see an opening.

15:11.896 --> 15:13.129
I knew it.

15:14.298 --> 15:17.968
Anything good in my life,
you have to take it away.

15:17.969 --> 15:20.570
"Oh, Charlie, you're so funny
and so clever.

15:20.571 --> 15:21.871
"Why don't I lean forward

15:21.872 --> 15:24.274
so you can look down my dress
and see my boobies?"

15:24.275 --> 15:27.844
"Why, thank you,
I believe I will."

15:27.845 --> 15:32.215
"So do you want to have sex now
or wait until after the party""

15:32.216 --> 15:33.950
"You don't mind
that I'm carrying most,

15:33.951 --> 15:35.952
if not all communicable diseases
known to man?"

15:35.953 --> 15:39.389
"Oh, no, Charlie,
that's part of your charm.

15:39.390 --> 15:41.558
Come, take me on the couch."

15:41.559 --> 15:43.760
"Are you sure?
It's not Scotchgarded."

15:43.761 --> 15:44.894
"No matter.

15:44.895 --> 15:47.497
We'll Scotchgard it
with our love."

15:51.902 --> 15:54.904
Uh...

15:54.905 --> 15:56.906
Hello, Mr. Skunk.

15:58.776 --> 15:59.909
Don't be alarmed.

15:59.910 --> 16:01.544
Uh, I was just leaving.

16:01.545 --> 16:05.782
Uh, there's, there's certainly
no reason to feel threatened.

16:06.684 --> 16:08.184
Good skunk.

16:08.185 --> 16:09.619
Nice skunk.

16:14.859 --> 16:16.893
Bad skunk!

16:19.897 --> 16:21.531
Oh, God, oh, God.

16:28.406 --> 16:30.540
Oh, God, oh, God.

16:32.376 --> 16:35.712
Who's out there?!

16:35.713 --> 16:36.746
Alan?

16:36.747 --> 16:37.781
Hey, Herb.

16:37.782 --> 16:39.382
Oh! Oh, wow!

16:40.685 --> 16:42.152
Hope you don't mind.

16:42.153 --> 16:43.720
I got skunked.

16:43.721 --> 16:45.555
Oh, you sure did.
Yeah.

16:45.556 --> 16:48.024
How come you're not
at Lyndsey's party?

16:48.025 --> 16:49.192
Oh, well, I wanted to,

16:49.193 --> 16:50.927
but Judith came down
with a sudden migraine.

16:50.928 --> 16:53.496
And by "migraine,"
I mean "bitch fit."

16:53.497 --> 16:55.298
Got it.

16:55.299 --> 16:56.466
How about you?

16:56.467 --> 16:57.834
Oh, Lyndsey and I

16:57.835 --> 16:59.302
had kind of a falling-out.

16:59.303 --> 17:02.205
'Cause you showed up
smelling like a skunk?

17:02.206 --> 17:04.340
No, no. Long story.

17:04.342 --> 17:06.175
I got time.

17:06.176 --> 17:08.178
I-I think she's fooling around

17:08.179 --> 17:10.280
with Charlie behind my back.

17:10.281 --> 17:11.647
Charlie?

17:11.648 --> 17:12.982
That lucky duck.

17:12.983 --> 17:14.217
What?

17:14.218 --> 17:16.886
I said, that son of a bitch.

17:16.887 --> 17:18.555
Story of my life.

17:18.556 --> 17:21.523
Uh, Wendy Freidman,
Kathy Bell, Amy Driskell.

17:21.525 --> 17:23.359
Amy Driskell?

17:23.361 --> 17:25.428
I lost my virginity
to Amy Driskell.

17:26.297 --> 17:28.231
You're kidding.

17:28.232 --> 17:30.266
Never even had to ask.

17:30.267 --> 17:31.601
Aah!

17:31.602 --> 17:32.635
It was our first date.

17:33.738 --> 17:35.238
Never got out of the driveway.

17:35.239 --> 17:36.706
Aw!

17:36.707 --> 17:38.208
We weren't even in a car.

17:39.510 --> 17:41.878
Hey, you know what's good
for getting rid of skunk smell?

17:41.879 --> 17:43.046
Tomato juice.

17:43.047 --> 17:44.180
Great. You got any?

17:44.181 --> 17:45.582
No.

17:46.584 --> 17:47.717
We might have some V-8.

17:47.718 --> 17:48.852
Think that'll work?

17:48.853 --> 17:50.220
Well, it sure doesn't taste

17:50.221 --> 17:51.421
like tomato juice,

17:51.422 --> 17:53.423
but you couldn't possibly
smell any worse.

17:53.424 --> 17:54.691
Hang on.

17:54.692 --> 17:56.025
Oh!

17:56.026 --> 17:58.762
What else could go wrong?

17:58.763 --> 18:00.897
Of course.

18:00.898 --> 18:03.466
I'm standing in dog crap.

18:03.467 --> 18:05.468
♪ Men. ♪

18:05.469 --> 18:07.637
I can't tell you
how happy it makes me

18:07.638 --> 18:10.006
to bring two friends
back together.

18:13.444 --> 18:15.678
Any better?

18:16.514 --> 18:18.748
Not really.

18:18.749 --> 18:20.617
Well, that's all the V-8.

18:20.618 --> 18:22.652
Want to try some ketchup?

18:22.653 --> 18:24.788
Why not?

18:25.823 --> 18:27.891
♪ Men. ♪

18:27.892 --> 18:30.260
I found this in one
of my son's shoes.

18:32.463 --> 18:35.131
Oh, yeah, I can get you
better than this.

18:35.132 --> 18:37.734
That's what
I was hoping.

18:37.735 --> 18:40.003
Lyndsey?!

18:42.106 --> 18:43.273
Alan?

18:43.274 --> 18:44.541
What the hell are you... ?

18:44.542 --> 18:45.875
Whoa!

18:45.876 --> 18:47.343
Where is he?

18:47.344 --> 18:48.711
Where is who?

18:48.712 --> 18:50.013
What is that smell?

18:50.014 --> 18:53.149
Skunk, dog crap and ketchup.
Oh.

18:53.150 --> 18:55.351
And don't try
to change the subject.

18:55.352 --> 18:57.320
Where is my brother?!

18:57.321 --> 19:00.056
Well, he-he left about
20 minutes ago with two women.

19:00.057 --> 19:01.958
Really?

19:01.959 --> 19:03.560
Really.

19:03.561 --> 19:05.695
So-so you and he aren't... ?

19:07.064 --> 19:09.132
That's what I've been
telling you, you smelly fool!

19:09.133 --> 19:11.167
Wow.

19:11.168 --> 19:13.236
Guess we had nothing
to fight about.

19:16.073 --> 19:18.274
Hug?

19:21.745 --> 19:25.148
I'll call you.

19:32.223 --> 19:33.857
You don't scare me.

19:33.858 --> 19:35.658
You already shot your load.

19:39.797 --> 19:43.733
Although I suppose
you could be a different skunk.

19:45.069 --> 19:49.172
♪ Men. ♪

19:50.444 --> 19:52.444
♪ Men. ♪

19:52.802 --> 19:54.936
So all I'm saying is,
given my history,

19:54.937 --> 19:57.005
Alan's paranoia is not
completely uncalled for.

19:57.006 --> 19:58.306
No, no, this wasn't paranoia.

19:58.307 --> 19:59.641
This was insanity.

19:59.642 --> 20:02.577
I know, I know, but...
The man was covered in ketchup.

20:02.578 --> 20:05.513
Well, to be fair,
there was a time in your life

20:05.514 --> 20:07.282
when you were covered
in frosting.

20:07.283 --> 20:09.017
It's not the same thing.

20:09.018 --> 20:11.519
I was putting myself
through college.

20:11.520 --> 20:15.357
Look, all I know is
that Alan really loves you.

20:15.358 --> 20:17.692
Now, if you ever repeat this,
I will deny it,

20:17.693 --> 20:20.628
but my brother is about the
most decent human being I know.

20:20.629 --> 20:22.864
Can't you just give
him one more chance?

20:22.865 --> 20:24.566
Well, I suppose.

20:25.735 --> 20:27.335
I knew it!

20:29.805 --> 20:31.806
You bastard!

20:31.807 --> 20:34.009
You slut!

20:37.847 --> 20:40.181
